## Issue 1 — Manager Directory & Email Resolution

**Priority:** P0 (blocks everything else)
**Estimate:** 4–5 days
**Labels:** `feature`, `backend`, `frontend`, `foundation`

### Context

Audit Excel uploads contain manager names but no emails. Without emails, no notification or tracking surface can function. We need a tenant-level directory that maps names → emails, handles misspellings, and learns from user corrections.

### Goals

- Single source of truth for manager contact info, scoped per tenant
- Three low-friction ingestion paths: file upload, paste-from-Excel, manual entry
- Fuzzy matching that auto-resolves high-confidence matches and surfaces ambiguous ones for human review
- Alias learning: a typo resolved once is never asked about again

### Non-goals

- Bi-directional sync with HR systems (future)
- Per-process directories (explicitly rejected — would cause re-entry)
- Auto-detection of manager roles or reporting chains

### Acceptance criteria

- [ ] New `ManagerDirectory` table with unique `(tenantId, email)` and indexed `normalizedKey`
- [ ] Upload wizard modal with 4 steps: drop-or-paste → column mapping → preview → commit
- [ ] Paste-from-Excel textarea handles tab-separated + newline input correctly
- [ ] Column auto-detection matches common header variants (`first_name`, `firstName`, `First Name`, `Given Name`)
- [ ] Preview step highlights duplicates, invalid emails, and conflicts with color-coded rows and a counts summary
- [ ] Matching function: exact `normalizedKey` → alias → fuzzy (token-sort ratio ≥ 0.90 auto-accept, 0.70–0.90 candidate list, <0.70 unmapped)
- [ ] Inline resolution drawer appears on any tile / Escalation Center page when unmapped managers exist
- [ ] Resolution drawer offers: accept suggestion (stores alias), "None of these" → inline add, "Apply all high-confidence" bulk action
- [ ] Directory management page at `/admin/directory` with search, filters, bulk archive, merge flow
- [ ] Merge repoints `TrackingEntry.managerKey` references to target entry; aliases folded in; source archived (never hard-deleted)
- [ ] Email changes on existing entries show "will repoint N tracking rows" confirmation
- [ ] Collision handling: two real people with the same name → forced to unmapped state, human must pick

### Technical scope

**Schema (Prisma):**

```prisma
model ManagerDirectory {
  id            String   @id
  tenantId      String
  firstName     String
  lastName      String
  email         String
  normalizedKey String
  aliases       Json     // string[] of observed spellings
  active        Boolean  @default(true)
  source        String   // "manual" | "upload" | "inline-resolved"
  createdBy     String?
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt

  @@unique([tenantId, email])
  @@index([tenantId, normalizedKey])
}
```

**Endpoints:**

- `POST /api/directory/upload` — accepts parsed rows, returns commit preview with diagnostics
- `POST /api/directory/commit` — applies with chosen strategy (`skip_duplicates` | `update_existing`)
- `POST /api/directory/resolve` — resolve unmapped name; records alias on success
- `POST /api/directory/merge` — merge two entries; returns affected row counts
- `GET /api/directory?search=...&filter=...` — paginated list for management page
- `GET /api/directory/:id/history` — all audit runs referencing this manager

**Components:**

- `<DirectoryUploadWizard />` — the 4-step modal
- `<PasteFromExcel />` — textarea with client-side TSV parser
- `<ResolutionDrawer />` — right-side drawer reusable on tile + Escalation Center
- `<DirectoryTable />` — admin page with inline edit, merge action

**Matching library:** `fastest-levenshtein` or `rapidfuzz-js`. Ship with conservative threshold (0.95 auto-accept), loosen based on real data in Issue 5 polish.

### Out of scope / deferred

- Bi-directional HR sync
- Auto-suggest emails from company SSO directory (add if Keycloak integration is desired later)
- Per-role permissions on directory editing (single admin role for v1)

