## Issue 2 — Escalation Data Model & State Machine

**Priority:** P0 (parallel to Issue 1)
**Estimate:** 3–4 days
**Labels:** `backend`, `foundation`, `schema-change`

### Context

Current `TrackingEntry` is process-scoped per manager (good), but `projectStatuses` is untyped JSON. We need a structured per-engine status model, a formal state machine, and an aggregation endpoint that unions findings across all 5 audit engines.

### Goals

- Formalize `projectStatuses` as typed `byEngine` structure with `aggregate` rollup
- Introduce `stage` as a finite-state enum with guarded transitions
- Build one aggregation endpoint that returns manager-centric rows for a process
- Log every state transition to `TrackingEvent` for full audit trail

### Non-goals

- Any UI work (that's Issue 3)
- Automatic transitions based on time (that's Issue 5)
- Template content or composer logic (that's Issue 4)

### Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `TrackingEntry.stage` constrained to enum: `NEW | DRAFTED | SENT | AWAITING_RESPONSE | RESPONDED | NO_RESPONSE | ESCALATED_L1 | ESCALATED_L2 | RESOLVED`
- [ ] `projectStatuses` JSON follows typed schema: `{ byEngine: { [engineKey]: { openCount, status, lastSeenRunId, resolvedAt? } }, aggregate: { totalOpen, overallStatus } }`
- [ ] Global `resolved = true` only when every non-`na` engine sub-status is `resolved`
- [ ] State transition function rejects illegal transitions (e.g. `RESOLVED → NEW` without explicit reopen)
- [ ] Every transition writes a `TrackingEvent` row with actor, timestamp, reason, payload
- [ ] New `NotificationTemplate` table created (content populated in Issue 4)
- [ ] `GET /api/processes/:id/escalations` returns manager-keyed rows aggregating issues from latest completed run per engine
- [ ] Aggregation normalizes manager email (lowercase, trim) for grouping
- [ ] Aggregation joins `ManagerDirectory` (from Issue 1) to attach emails when available
- [ ] Re-run audit auto-reconciles: engine sub-status flips to `resolved` if manager no longer flagged; other engines untouched
- [ ] Unit tests cover all legal transitions + rejection of all illegal ones

### Technical scope

**Schema:**

```prisma
enum EscalationStage {
  NEW
  DRAFTED
  SENT
  AWAITING_RESPONSE
  RESPONDED
  NO_RESPONSE
  ESCALATED_L1
  ESCALATED_L2
  RESOLVED
}

model TrackingEntry {
  // ...existing fields...
  stage           EscalationStage @default(NEW)
  slaDueAt        DateTime?
  escalationLevel Int             @default(0)
  // projectStatuses JSON now typed per spec above
}

model NotificationTemplate {
  id          String   @id
  tenantId    String?  // null = system template
  parentId    String?  // org override points at system template
  stage       String
  subject     String
  body        String
  channel     String   // "email" | "teams" | "both"
  active      Boolean
  version     Int
  createdBy   String
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt
}
```

**Server modules:**

- `EscalationStateMachine` — pure function `canTransition(from, to): boolean` + `transition(entry, to, actor, reason): TrackingEntry`
- `EscalationAggregator` — builds manager-keyed rows from latest runs
- `StatusReconciler` — runs after each audit; updates byEngine sub-statuses

**Endpoints:**

- `GET /api/processes/:id/escalations` — the main read endpoint (returns rows for UI in Issue 3)
- `POST /api/tracking/:id/transition` — explicit transition trigger (used by composer in Issue 4)

**Migration:**

- Backfill existing `TrackingEntry.projectStatuses` into new structured format
- Default `stage` derived from existing `resolved` flag: `resolved=true → RESOLVED`, else `NEW`

### Out of scope / deferred

- UI to visualize the state machine (nice-to-have admin tool, post-MVP)
- Cross-process aggregation (single process per page for now)

