## Issue 3 — Escalation Center UI & Tile Cleanup

**Priority:** P0 (depends on Issues 1 + 2)
**Estimate:** 5–6 days
**Labels:** `frontend`, `feature`, `breaking-ux`

### Context

This is the user-visible payoff. One page, one row per manager, engine findings visible as pills. Tiles get demoted to pure analysis surfaces — no more per-tile Send button, no more per-tile TrackingTab.

### Goals

- Ship the Escalation Center as a top-level route on each process
- Make cross-engine manager exposure visible at a glance
- Remove the duplication-inducing per-tile workflow
- Preserve tile analysis capability (files, runs, versions, evidence)

### Non-goals

- Composer or send capability (that's Issue 4 — Center is read-only at end of this issue)
- Bulk operations (that's Issue 5)
- Template editing (that's Issue 4)

### Acceptance criteria

**New page (`/processes/:id/escalations`):**

- [ ] Left filter rail: stage (checkboxes), engine, SLA status, assigned-to-me toggle, saved views stub
- [ ] Center manager table with columns: manager (name + email), total issues, engine pills (count per engine, greyed when zero), stage badge, last contact, SLA dot (green/amber/red), row action menu
- [ ] Sort by total issues / stage / last contact / SLA
- [ ] Keyboard navigation: `j`/`k` to move between rows, `enter` to open panel, `esc` to close
- [ ] Right slide-over panel on row click (no page navigation)
- [ ] Panel has 4 tabs: **Findings** (grouped by engine, expandable, deep-link to tile evidence), **Compose** (placeholder in this issue), **Activity** (TrackingEvent timeline), **Attachments** (placeholder)
- [ ] Panel header shows manager, email, stage badge, SLA countdown
- [ ] Top summary bar: total open findings, per-engine counts, managers-with-open count, SLA-breaching count

**Process dashboard changes:**

- [ ] Banner above tile grid when unresolved escalations exist: "N managers have open findings across M engines. [Open Escalation Center →]"
- [ ] Footer chip on each tile: "N managers flagged here" — deep-links to Escalation Center pre-filtered to that engine

**Tile cleanup:**

- [ ] Remove `<TrackingTab />` from tile workspace (or demote to read-only "Evidence for this engine")
- [ ] Remove per-tile "Send notification" buttons
- [ ] Tile retains: file upload, run audit, version history, issue list as evidence view
- [ ] Add small "email" column to tile issue list populated from directory (gap visible where unmapped)

**Unmapped manager handling:**

- [ ] `<ResolutionDrawer />` from Issue 1 surfaces on Escalation Center when unmapped managers exist
- [ ] Non-blocking banner: "N managers in these findings aren't in the directory. Notifications can't be sent until they're resolved."

### Technical scope

**Routes:**

- `/processes/:id/escalations` (new)
- `/processes/:id` (existing — add banner + tile chips)
- Tile route (existing — remove TrackingTab route)

**Components:**

- `<EscalationCenter />` — page shell, filter rail, table, panel orchestrator
- `<ManagerTable />` — dense row rendering with pills, keyboard handlers
- `<EnginePill />` — reusable, takes `engine`, `count`, `onClick`
- `<EscalationPanel />` — slide-over with tabs
- `<FindingsTab />` — groups findings by engine, each linking to evidence
- `<ActivityFeed />` — renders `TrackingEvent[]` chronologically
- `<ProcessDashboardBanner />` — unresolved-escalations summary
- `<TileEscalationChip />` — footer chip on each tile

**Data:**

- Consumes `GET /api/processes/:id/escalations` from Issue 2
- Panel consumes `GET /api/tracking/:id/events` for activity feed

**Migration / breaking changes:**

- Feature flag the old TrackingTab for 1 release cycle, then remove
- Document the change in release notes — this is a visible UX shift

### Out of scope / deferred

- Composer functionality (Issue 4)
- Saved views persistence (Issue 5 polish)
- Advanced filters (date ranges, custom tags)

