## Issue 4 — Template System, Composer & Send Workflow

**Priority:** P1 (depends on Issue 3)
**Estimate:** 5–6 days
**Labels:** `frontend`, `backend`, `feature`

### Context

Single-manager send flow. Three-layer templates (system / org override / per-send edit), slot substitution, state transitions on send. This is where the escalation becomes *actionable*.

### Goals

- Admins manage templates; users send with minimal friction
- Every send moves state machine forward atomically
- One notification record per send, even when multiple engines are included
- Preview flip so users see exactly what the recipient sees

### Non-goals

- Bulk send (Issue 5)
- Scheduled send (Issue 5)
- Auto-escalation drafts (Issue 5)

### Acceptance criteria

**Template admin (`/admin/templates`):**

- [ ] List-detail layout grouped by stage, system templates locked with lock icon
- [ ] "Clone to customize" creates org override (parentId set)
- [ ] Editor shows slot reference sidebar: `{managerFirstName}`, `{processName}`, `{findingsByEngine}`, `{slaDeadline}`, `{auditRunDate}`, `{auditorName}`
- [ ] Preview pane renders template against a sample manager with real slot substitution
- [ ] Publish creates new version; old versions remain queryable; new sends use latest active
- [ ] Channel toggle per template: email / teams / both

**Composer (modal, triggered from panel "Compose" tab or row action):**

- [ ] Recipient block: locked manager, auto-populated CC based on stage (L1 → manager's manager, L2 → stakeholder)
- [ ] CCs removable with warning
- [ ] Template picker pre-selected based on current stage; changing warns if user edited body
- [ ] Subject field (editable, slot-expanded)
- [ ] Body field (markdown or minimal rich text, slot-expanded)
- [ ] `{findingsByEngine}` renders as collapsible sections per engine; each section deletable with warning ("N findings still open in tracking")
- [ ] Channel toggle defaults from template
- [ ] Preview toggle flips composer to read-only rendered view
- [ ] Bottom bar: Discard · Save draft · Send

**Send mechanics:**

- [ ] Send triggers: one SMTP/Teams call, one `NotificationsService.recordSend`, one state transition, one `TrackingEvent`
- [ ] `recordSend` persists resolved (post-substitution) body and structured `{ sources: [engineKeys] }`
- [ ] State transitions enforced: NEW → DRAFTED (on save draft), NEW/DRAFTED → SENT (on send), SENT → AWAITING_RESPONSE (immediately after send)
- [ ] SLA clock starts on transition to AWAITING_RESPONSE
- [ ] `outlookCount` / `teamsCount` incremented per channel
- [ ] Soft lock: if another user has DRAFTED state open, second user sees read-only "Being edited by X" warning

**Learning loop (subtle):**

- [ ] After 3rd identical manual edit to the same template, offer "Save these changes to org template"

### Technical scope

**Endpoints:**

- `GET /api/templates?stage=...` — list templates (system + org override merged)
- `POST /api/templates` — create org override
- `PATCH /api/templates/:id` — edit + version bump
- `POST /api/tracking/:id/compose` — save draft (transitions to DRAFTED)
- `POST /api/tracking/:id/send` — send (transitions to SENT → AWAITING_RESPONSE)
- `POST /api/tracking/:id/preview` — returns resolved subject + body for preview

**Components:**

- `<TemplateAdmin />` — list-detail page
- `<TemplateEditor />` — editor with slot sidebar + preview
- `<Composer />` — modal triggered from panel
- `<EngineSectionBlock />` — collapsible findings section inside composer body
- `<PreviewPane />` — renders final email/teams message

**Slot substitution:**

- Pure function: `substitute(template: string, slots: Slots): string`
- Slot values resolved server-side to keep logic canonical
- `{findingsByEngine}` expands into formatted markdown/HTML blocks

### Out of scope / deferred

- Response parsing (Issue 5)
- A/B testing templates (never)
- Attachments on outgoing emails (evaluate post-MVP)

