## Issue 5 — SLA Engine, Bulk Operations & Polish

**Priority:** P1 (depends on Issue 4)
**Estimate:** 5–6 days
**Labels:** `backend`, `frontend`, `automation`, `polish`

### Context

Makes the workflow self-driving. Cron-based SLA enforcement, auto-queued (never auto-sent) escalations, bulk compose, in-app notifications, saved views, keyboard shortcuts, scheduled sends. The "this actually feels like a real product" issue.

### Goals

- Users never need to manually check who's overdue — the system tells them
- Bulk send turns "12 managers × 3 engines = 36 emails" into one workflow pass
- No surprise sends: everything stays human-reviewed

### Non-goals

- Machine-learning-based response classification (future)
- SMS / WhatsApp channels (future)

### Acceptance criteria

**SLA engine:**

- [ ] Scheduled job runs every N minutes (default 15)
- [ ] For each `TrackingEntry` in `SENT` or `AWAITING_RESPONSE` past `slaDueAt`: transition to `NO_RESPONSE`, auto-queue L1 draft, notify auditor in-app
- [ ] For each in `ESCALATED_L1` past `slaDueAt + L2Delay`: transition to `NO_RESPONSE` (L2), auto-queue L2 draft, notify auditor + their lead
- [ ] **Drafts are queued, never auto-sent** — user must click to send
- [ ] Idempotent: no duplicate drafts for same (entry, stage)
- [ ] SLA config per tenant: initial SLA hours, L1 delay, L2 delay

**Bulk operations:**

- [ ] Multi-select rows in Escalation Center → top bar transforms to bulk actions
- [ ] Bulk compose opens multi-tab preview: one tab per recipient, each showing their fully-rendered email
- [ ] Each tab individually editable before send-all
- [ ] "Send all N" fires sequentially with progress indicator; failures isolated, rest continue
- [ ] Bulk mark resolved / bulk snooze / bulk escalate

**In-app notifications:**

- [ ] Bell icon in top nav with unread count
- [ ] Dropdown feed: "Manager X responded" (with inline preview), "N escalations breached SLA — drafts ready", "Your scheduled send just went out"
- [ ] Click notification → deep-link into Escalation Center with correct row open
- [ ] Mark all read

**Daily digest email:**

- [ ] 9am local time email to each auditor with open escalations
- [ ] Summary only: counts + deep-links, not per-event
- [ ] Opt-out in user preferences

**Scheduled sends:**

- [ ] Composer "Send now" / "Send at [datetime]" toggle
- [ ] Scheduled sends appear in Activity feed as pending event
- [ ] Cancelable before firing
- [ ] Fires via same send pipeline; same state transitions apply

**Response detection (basic):**

- [ ] Webhook / polling integration for reply detection (scope to Outlook first)
- [ ] Reply to tracked email → transition to `RESPONDED`, notify auditor
- [ ] Reply body stored on `TrackingEvent`

**Saved views:**

- [ ] Save current filter combination with a name
- [ ] Appear in left rail of Escalation Center
- [ ] Defaults seeded: "My overdue," "L2 escalations," "Awaiting my review"

**Keyboard shortcuts:**

- [ ] `c` compose, `r` resolve, `e` escalate now, `s` snooze, `/` focus search
- [ ] `?` shows shortcut cheat sheet
- [ ] `j`/`k` navigation confirmed from Issue 3

**Matching threshold tuning (follow-up to Issue 1):**

- [ ] Review real match confidence distribution
- [ ] Adjust auto-accept threshold based on observed false positive rate

### Technical scope

**Background jobs:**

- `SLAEnforcer` — cron, transitions + draft queue
- `ScheduledSendDispatcher` — cron, fires scheduled sends at their time
- `ResponseWatcher` — webhook handler or polling loop

**Endpoints:**

- `POST /api/tracking/bulk/compose` — returns N previews
- `POST /api/tracking/bulk/send` — fires N sends with progress stream (SSE)
- `GET /api/notifications` — in-app feed
- `POST /api/notifications/:id/read` — mark read
- `GET /api/views` / `POST /api/views` — saved view CRUD

**Components:**

- `<NotificationBell />` — top nav bell + dropdown
- `<BulkComposer />` — tabbed multi-recipient preview
- `<ShortcutOverlay />` — `?` cheat sheet
- `<SavedViewsRail />` — left rail section

### Out of scope / deferred

- Full NLP response classification
- Non-Outlook reply detection (Gmail, etc.) — can layer in later
- Analytics dashboard (response rates, time-to-resolution) — separate future issue

